    <h2> What is the World Wide Web ?</h2>
    <p>
        The World Wide Web (WWW) is a system of interlinked 
        web pages that are accessed through the internet using web browsers.
        It allows users to access information in the form of web pages,
         which may contain text, images, videos and hperlinks to other pages.
    </p>

    <p>It is important to note that the World Wide Web is not the same as the Internet. 
        The internet is the physical network infrastructure (cables, routers and servers). 
        While the WWW is a service that operates on top pf the Internet using specific protocols.

    </p>
    <h2> How the World Wide Web works</h2>
    <p>
        The WWW operates based on a client-server model. When a user wants to access a website,
        they enter a Uniform Resource Locator(URL) into a web srver using the Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP).

    </p>
    <p> 
        The process works as follows:

    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>The user enters a URL into the browser.</li>
            <li>The Domain Name System (DNS) translates the domain name into an IP address.</li>
            <li>The browser sends an HTTP request to the web server.</li>
            <li>The web server processes the request and sends back the requested web page.</li>
            <li>The browser renders the page using HTML, CSS and JavaScript</li>

        </ol>
        
    </p>
